00:57:54.840 --> 00:57:59.010
I'd be really nervous if we
relied on science to tell us

00:57:59.010 --> 00:58:01.860
what human flourishing is.

00:58:01.860 --> 00:58:04.650
The sciences do two
things, don't they?

00:58:04.650 --> 00:58:08.640
They attempt to rigorously
describe regularities

00:58:08.640 --> 00:58:10.570
in the natural world.

00:58:10.570 --> 00:58:13.360
And then they attempt to
generate causal explanations

00:58:13.360 --> 00:58:16.180
for those regularities.

00:58:16.180 --> 00:58:19.690
So in Aristotelian
terms, science

00:58:19.690 --> 00:58:22.930
proposes efficient
causes of things.

00:58:22.930 --> 00:58:25.750
Aristotle also talked
about final causes.

00:58:25.750 --> 00:58:30.520
He talked about the ends for
which things are constructed.

00:58:30.520 --> 00:58:33.760
And his notion of nature,
for example, of human nature

00:58:33.760 --> 00:58:37.530
or the nature of anything
was highly teleological,

00:58:37.530 --> 00:58:39.790
that we had a particular end.

00:58:39.790 --> 00:58:45.250
And in his view, and in the view
probably of most of us here,

00:58:45.250 --> 00:58:50.650
if there is an end, if
there is a normative telos,

00:58:50.650 --> 00:58:55.060
and we miss it, well,
that's called tragedy,

00:58:55.060 --> 00:58:59.740
or in physical context,
it's called illness.

00:58:59.740 --> 00:59:03.340
But science can't
decide what that end is,

00:59:03.340 --> 00:59:06.190
nor, contra Dawkins,
can it decide

00:59:06.190 --> 00:59:08.690
whether there is such an end.

00:59:08.690 --> 00:59:16.010
So my definition of
flourishing, in my own life,

00:59:16.010 --> 00:59:17.510
well, even before
I was a Christian,

00:59:17.510 --> 00:59:22.130
I thought that
ultimately flourishing

00:59:22.130 --> 00:59:26.150
was to have a matrix of intimate
and loving relationships

00:59:26.150 --> 00:59:30.290
with other folks with
whom I could be myself,

00:59:30.290 --> 00:59:32.660
they could be
their selves to me,

00:59:32.660 --> 00:59:37.120
and for whom we would be
invested in one another.

00:59:37.120 --> 00:59:41.920
But, speaking
autobiographically,

00:59:41.920 --> 00:59:44.890
and I am so grateful
I've had that in my life,

00:59:44.890 --> 00:59:46.780
but that wasn't enough.

00:59:46.780 --> 00:59:50.260
And I actually construe
ultimate flourishing

00:59:50.260 --> 00:59:52.270
in the Augustinian terms.

00:59:52.270 --> 00:59:55.280
You have made us for
yourself, and the heart

00:59:55.280 --> 00:59:58.080
is restless til it
finds its rest in you.

00:59:58.080 --> 01:00:05.610
That flourishing is loving
embrace of and by our creator

01:00:05.610 --> 01:00:07.570
who made us specifically
for that end.

